    B --> C[State]
    C --> D[Broker API]
```
```

## When to Create/Update

**Create README.md when:**
- New folder with 2+ files is created
- Existing folder has no README.md

**Update README.md when:**
- Files are added, removed, or renamed
- File purposes change significantly
- New commands are introduced
- Architecture changes

## Maintenance Process

1. **During changes**: Update README in the same folder you modified
2. **Walk up**: Check if parent folder READMEs need updates
3. **Before finishing**: Verify all touched folders have current READMEs

## Quality Checklist

Before considering a README complete:
- [ ] Purpose is clear in 1-2 sentences
- [ ] All files are listed with descriptions
- [ ] Commands section exists if folder has runnable scripts
- [ ] Mermaid diagrams added where they clarify relationships
- [ ] No stale references to deleted files
